wikipedia_page.main: Peter Baker (born 24 August 1934) is an English former footballer. He played League football as a fullback for Sheffield Wednesday and Queens Park Rangers.Baker started his career as an amateur at Tottenham Hotspur before joining Sheffield Wednesday at the start of the 1957-58 season. During his spell at Hillsborough he made eleven league appearances and also played in one FA Cup match.
